1.) Explain what the terminal is in your own words.
The terminal is a command line interface where we can input commands directly into the computer to complete system tasks more efficiently.

2.) What is the major difference between Git and Github?
Git is a version control system that allows us to track versions/changes of files. Github is a cloud where we can save our files in repositories.

3.) Why do we use Github?
It is a cloud where we can upload our files and a way that we can collaborate with others as a team on the files of others.